director alan spoon director   prevprev bio alan spoonnextnext bio alan spoon richard f zannino director richard f zannino director   prevprev bio richard f zanninonextnext bio richard f zannino overview leadership history iac cares news button scroll up chris terrill  wikipedia chris terrill from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search for the american chief executive see chris terrill executive chris terrill chris terrill is a british anthropologist adventurer author and filmmaker contents  biography  personal life  books published  film history  awards  nominations  notes  references  external links biographyedit born in brighton sussex in  terrill attended brighton college –0 and then went to durham university where he gained a jointhonours degree in geography and anthropology between  and  he lived with the remote acholi tribe of southern sudan where he carried out doctoral research on the impact of civil war on the tribal society before taking up the post of head of geography at rendcomb college in gloucestershire in  he left teaching to become a fulltime professional anthropologist working for the international disaster institute and the un in geneva and throughout the famine gripped and war ravaged areas of africa later and quite by accident he moved into broadcasting when he went to give an interview to the bbc african service and was offered a job on the spot he changed careers and became a producer for the bbc world service specialising in african affairs after five years in radio in which he specialised in current affairs documentaries and drama terrill joined bbc television as a documentary producer making investigative documentaries and observational films and series about communities all over the world as a programme maker terrill has always favoured anthropological methodology particularly participant observationnote  rather than more conventional documentary making techniques as a fellow of the royal anthropological institute and the royal geographical society terrill is regarded as a practising anthropologistgeographer who uses film as his primary research tool and recording medium in the field he won an emmy for outstanding investigative journalism for a film called ape trade this inside story special bbc exposed the major gangs smuggling endangered orangutans to illegal markets in taiwan the usa and russianote  after 0 years at the bbc and with over 00 prime time films to his name he left the corporation in 00 to set up his own company uppercut films and began to specialise in military and high adventure documentariesnote —though always concentrating on communitiesgroups and their internal dynamics in 00 he documented and participated in the rigorous eight months training with the royal marine commandos after which he followed the newly qualified recruits to the front line in afghanistan for their first taste of real war terrill is the first civilian to complete and pass all four commando tests for which he was awarded an honorary green beretnote  terrill produces his own camerawork and sound recording without a film crew this lone wolf technique is a hallmark of his work using the new digital technology he was the first mainstream filmmaker to experiment as a selfshootingselfrecording director in the mid 0s when he made soho stories for the bbc a series that won him the coveted royal television society award for innovation this seminal series a colourful and highly revealing portrait of londons glamorous soho district was one of the first to use the docusoap style of filmmaking0 widely credited as the father of the docusoap though both paul watson and jeremy mills have similar claim to the title terrill then went on to refine his techniques on prime time series such as the cruise bbc jailbirds bbcnote  through the eyes of the old bbc the ship bbc shipmates bbc  and two feature documentary specials on charlotte church—spreading her wings bbc and confessions of a teenangel itv commando on the front line itv—an account of royal marine commandos fighting in afghanistan was followed by natures fury itv a trilogy on the worlds greatest storms and their impact on communitiesnote  in 00 terrill made a series on the theatre royal haymarket london called theatreland this was an intimate portrait of theatre people at work and featured ian mckellen patrick stewart and anna friel in the same year he made a twopart film series about royal marines badly injured in afghanistan attempting to climb in the high himalayas wartorn warriors—skynote  in 00 he spent six months on hms manchester in the caribbean filming counter narcotics operations as well as humanitarian disaster relief during the hurricane season royal navy caribbean patrol for channel five and national geographic in 0 terrill returned to working with the royal marines when he joined  commando in the dangerous nad e ali north district of helmand province this was for a part series commissioned by channel five entitled royal marines mission afghanistan transmitted in januaryfebruary 0 in late 0 terrill embarked on a project that brought together the military and the theatre the theatre royal haymarket where terrill had filmed theatreland in 00 put on a play using injured soldiers and marines as the actors singers and dancers the play written by the poet owen sheers and based on the experiences of the soldiers mostly in afghanistan was called the two worlds of charlie f and was performed on  january 0 terrills featurelength film entitled theatre of war documenting the preparation of the play was shown on bbcs imagine strand and was nominated for a prestigious grierson award in the best arts documentary category in 0 terrills current affairs film for the bbc marine a criminal or casualty of war won the evcom clarion award for ethics in journalism in 0 terrill became a fellow of the maritime foundation and was presented with a lifetime achievement award terrill lectures widely on film making techniques – especially on working solo in the field he holds regular workshops at the london film school personal lifeedit in  terrill was engaged for a brief period to former glamour model heather mills he proposed to her on a fishing boat whilst sailing up the mekong river in cambodia where they were making a film about landmines terrill is now married to the bafta awardwinning filmmaker christine hall on  february 0 terrill received a full apology in open court from news group for repeatedly hacking his phone in 000 they also paid undisclosed but substantial damages plus costs terrill is an accomplished amateur athlete specialising in ultra running triathlon rugby and boxing books publishededit year title publisher synopsis  hms brilliant bbc books the book describes the events that took place on the hms brilliant a royal navy frigate on front line duty in the adriatic during the yugoslavian war as part of operation sharp guard 00 shipmates century random house an exploration of the british royal navys heritage and its role in the modern world 00 commando arrow books random house chris terrills experience of training with the elite royal marines commandos and winning his own green beret before following them to the front line in afghanistan film historyedit year filmtelevision series broadcaster summary  subway inside story bbc crime and violence on the london underground 0 bullies 0 minutes bbc the chronic problem of school bullying 0 the race game inside story bbc an investigation into racism in british sport 0 fit to drop 0 minutes bbc the extraordinary story of people addicted to exercise  brief encounters 0 minutes bbc prostitutes pimps punters and the police at kings cross railway station  ape trade inside story special bbcnational geographic undercover investigation into international orangutan smuggling  yellow line inside story bbc the vicious parking wars on the streets of london  miami wild 0 minutes bbc policing the animal smuggling trade in florida  seeing red inside story bbc union unrest crime and violence on londons buses  the women trade inside story special bbc undercover investigation into international prostitution and the marketing of women for the sex industry  beloved country bbc part series on ordinary south african lives as the country approached full democracy and black rule  hms brilliant bbc part series on a royal navy warship serving during the yugoslavian war  alisons last mountain inside story special bbc journey to k with the family of alison hargreaves soon after her death on the mountain  soho stories bbc  part series about life in londons famous and flamboyant soho district  the cruise bbc  part series on board a luxury cruise ship in the caribbean featuring jane mcdonald  jane ties the knot bbc  cruise special—jane gets married on a caribbean island  janes cruise to the stars bbc  cruise special—janes rise to stardom  jailbirds bbc  0part series inside newhall womens high security prison  beyond the bars bbc  jailbirds special—what happened to the prisoners after release  titos story bbc  inside story special on an yearold autistic boy in india who writes beautiful philosophical poetry  the quest bbc  the story of a rock gospel band and their bid for fame 00 through the eyes of the old bbc  0minute feature on being old 00 through the eyes of the young bbc  0minute feature on being young 00 the ship bbc history channel part adventure series sailing the endeavour in the wake of captain cook from australia to indonesia 00 shaylers secrets bbc  following the rogue spy david shayler through his fateful trial at the old bailey 00 charlotte church—spreading her wings bbc  a year in the life of the young diva as she approaches her th birthday 00 the making of sheila quigley bbc  the extraordinary story of a first time novelist 00 debra winger in africa charity film film for sightsavers international about debra winger visiting kenya to highlight the plight of the blind 00 the  hour plays charity film film for the old vic about a unique theatrical experiment 00 charlotte church—confessions of a teen angel itv charlotte attempting to break into the rock world 00–00 shipmates bbc  a major part series about the royal navy on operations 00 debra winger in india charity film a film for sightsavers international about debra winger visiting india to highlight the plight of the blind 00 the sultan and the elephant bbc four the heartwarming story of a giant elephants visit to the streets of london and the enchantment he brought with him 00 extreme theatre sky tv a onehour special on a unique theatrical experiment at the old vic featuring kevin spacey 00 commando—on the front line itv part series on the royal marines serving on the front line in afghanistan 00 the  year old commando itv and  the story of chris terrills attempt to win the iconic green beret of the royal marines commando directed by malcolm donkin 00 commando—on the front line directors cut itv part series as above—one hour versions 00 the parish church of england—st martininthefields five part series on a year in the life of this iconic church in trafalgar square 00 go commando itv two royal marines row the atlantic ocean 00 natures fury itv part series on the worlds most destructive storms and their impact on communities tornadoes hurricanes and firestorms 00 theatreland sky arts part series behind the scenes at the famous theatre royal haymarket featuring ian mckellen patrick stuart ronald pickup simon callow and anna friel 00 war torn warriors sky  two 0minute films about badly injured royal marines trekking and climbing in the high himalayas 0 royal navy caribbean patrol fivenational geographic fivepart series about the royal navy tracking down cocaine smugglers and providing humanitarian relief after hurricane strikes in the caribbean 0 natures fury—monsoon itv facing up to the extremes of the indian monsoon 0 royal marines mission afghanistan five sixpart series on the royal marines of  commando working in the nad e ali north district of helmand province known at the time as the most dangerous square mile in the world 0 theatre of war bbc theatre presents war in a unique and remarkable way for a featurelength imagine special 0 battle scarred five fourpart series on the problems faced by exservicemen when returning to civilian life 0 living on the edge  blood in the snow five following the great reindeer migration across northern norway with the sami nomads  the oldest living culture in europe 0 living on the edge  blood in the sand five a journey across the drought belt of africa from mali to northern kenya and into war ravaged somalia 0 living on the edge  blood in the sea five fishing with the senegalese and mauritanian fishermen in the dangerous waters off the west coast of africa 0 marine a criminal or casualty of war bbc a personal exploration into the ethical and moral issues of a battle field execution 0 commando return to the front line itv a onehour special updating the story of commando on the front line the film follows bertie kerr back to afghanistan to assess the legacy of a war that cost over  british lives 0 the commando who refused to die forces tv the moving and inspiring story of corporal paul vice mc who suffered horrific life changing injuries after being blown up in afghanistan but who then reinvented his life in the most extraordinary way 0 return to the jungle forces tv veterans from the parachute regiment return to borneo for the 0th anniversary of the battle of plaman mapu in   paras held out against 00 troops of the indonesian special forces in a desperate battle described as a latter day rorkes drift 0 royal marine wags and the great yomp forces tv royal marines wives and girlfriends  the bootneckettes  attempt the great yomp 0 miles over the south downs way in  hours non stop giant blisters are the least of their problems 0 royal navy strike carrier bbc threepart series the epic story of hms queen elizabeth  the biggest warship ever built for the royal navy from first day of build to maiden voyage this will be the story of a state of the art warship the people who built her the people who will sail her and also the people who will fly off her  in production  to hell and back forces tv the story of an heroic attempt by eight royal marines to break the world speed marching record  a full marathon running as a troop in full fighting order wearing combat boots and carrying 0lbs rucksack plus weapon a moving tale of determination courage and comradeship in production  marine a the inside story panorama bbc a panorama special on the marine a murder case 0 wildlife warriors bbc former british soldiers confront the animal poachers in india and africa in production awardsedit year type filmtelevision series broadcaster category  emmy ape trade bbcnational geographic outstanding investigative journalism  broadcast award hms brilliant bbc best producerdirector  royal television society award soho stories bbc innovation 00 emma ethnic and multicultural media award titos story bbc best documentary 0 clarion award for ethical journalism marine a criminal or casualty of war bbc best current affairs documentary 0 the maritime fellowship award special distinction a twenty year body of work relating to maritime matters associated with the royal navy and the royal marines tv all channels radio and the written word lifetime achievement award nominationsedit year type filmtelevision series broadcaster category  bafta craft awards soho stories bbc best sound  national tv awards the cruise bbc best factual series 00 bafta through the eyes of the old bbc best single documentary 00 grierson through the eyes of the old bbc best documentary on a contemporary theme 00 emmy the ship bbchistory channel cinematography 00 education on tv awards the ship bbchistory channel best documentary series highly recommended 00 maritime media awards shipmates bbc best documentary series 00 mental health awards war torn warriors sky  best documentary 0 maritime media awards royal navy caribbean patrol channel five best documentary series 0 grierson theatre of war bbc  best arts documentary 0 maritime media awards blood in the sea channel five best documentary film notesedit  participant observation—a type of research strategy it is a widely used methodology in many disciplines particularly cultural anthropology but also sociology communication studies and social psychology its aim is to gain a close and intimate familiarity with a given group of individuals such as a religious occupational or sub cultural group or a particular community and their practices through an intensive involvement with people in their natural environment usually over an extended period of time  to achieve this terrill went undercover as a wildlife smuggler in a later film called women trade that exposed criminal gangs trading in women from the developing world for the sex market in europe terrill posed as a woman trader in the dominican republic as well as in denmark and belgium  uppercut also has a small but vibrant arts department which specialises in theatre based films due to terrills passion for live theatre when you have your own film company you can choose what films you want to make—it is like having a massive toybox full of all your favourite toys and you can keep getting new ones terrill sept 00 when asked why he chose to make theatreland at the same time as working with the royal marines  jimmy savile was a previous recipient of the honorary green beret although he did not attempt all four commando tests in any case since the scandal over his activities with under age girls savile has been posthumously stripped of his honorary green beret gethin jones attempted the last of the tests the 0mile run across dartmoor but finished in a time of  hours 0 minutes – 0 minutes over the pass time of  hours  for this series terrill spent eight months in prison  terrill has established a reputation as the thinking mans adventurer his quests invariably lead him to the worlds hotspots and his focus is usually on the victims of war poverty or natural hazards his approach is analytical and searching and his films are not typical made for tv adventure the radio times published one article about terrills work which was titled rather provocatively meet the explorer who makes bear grylls look like barbie  this series was shortlisted for the 00 mind mental health media awards and one of the films main contributors marine danny claricoates received the speaking out award for his courage in talking so openly about his own post traumatic stress disorder after seeing his two best friends blown up and killed in front of him referencesedit  the creation of the acholi minority their dispersal as refugees and their repatriation – durham university geography department   the second international conference on assistance to refugees in africa disasters vol  issue  december   rural refugees in africa past experience future pointers r chambers disasters vol  issue  march   anthropologist about town royal anthropological institute going commando 0 september 00  commando chris terrill random house 00  international primate protection league vol  no  aug  bbc exposes ape trade  the national archives defencenews  december 00 the hardest embed going native with the royal marines  manchester evening news ian wylie  september 00 chris—right in the line of fire  new documentary a critical introduction stella bruzzi pgs   new challenges for documentary alan rosenthal john corner  understanding realitytelevision su holmes deborah jermyn pge   frames and fictions on television the politics of identity within bruce carson margaret llewellyn jones  independent a docusoap worthy of the hard cell brian viner  march   how i captured the perfect storm broadcast  june 00  httpwwwradiotimescomnews00survivingthearcticandthedesertmeettheexplorerwhomakesbeargryllslooklikebarbie external linksedit commando on the front line jon stratford—pti 